{"verses": ["Upon you my fellow servants, in the name of Messiah I  confer the  Priesthood of Aaron, which holds the  keys of the ministering of  angels, and of the gospel of  repentance, and of  baptism by immersion for the remission of sins; and this shall never be taken again from the earth, until the sons of  Levi do offer again an offering unto the Lord in  righteousness."], "more_summary": "Keys and powers of Aaronic Priesthood are set forth.", "book_name": "Section", "summary": "Ordination of Joseph Smith and Oliver Cowdery to the Aaronic Priesthood along the bank of the Susquehanna River, near Harmony, Pennsylvania, May 15, 1829.   HC 1: 39\u201342.   The ordination was done by the hands of an angel, who announced himself as John, the same that is called John the Baptist in the New Testament.   The angel explained that he was acting under the direction of Peter, James, and John, the ancient apostles, who held the keys of the higher priesthood, which was called the Priesthood of Melchizedek.   The promise was given to Joseph and Oliver that in due time the Priesthood of Melchizedek would be conferred upon them.   See also Section 27: 7, 8, 12."}